  "commentary": "With SPX at 6597.01 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6590 and max positive gamma at 6605, dealers are caught in a narrow but volatile pocket where they're buying dips into 6590 and selling rallies into 6605, creating whipsaw action in this tight 15-point range. The breakout regime with -7.2B total GEX means any sustained move outside this range will see dealers amplify the direction—if we break above 6605, expect acceleration higher as dealers chase the move, while a drop below 6590 should see momentum selling. Watch for a decisive break of either 6590 or 6605, as the massive gamma walls at these strikes will determine whether we get explosive moves or remain trapped in this high-volatility chop zone.\n\nBottom line: expect violent swings between 6590 and 6605 until one level breaks decisively.",
